00:20:42,541 --> 00:20:45,169
Are you going, too?

250
00:20:46,011 --> 00:20:47,911
I have to get up early.

251
00:20:48,013 --> 00:20:50,538
I can run you home later.

252
00:20:51,883 --> 00:20:55,046
Stay on. I'm leaving you
in good hands.

253
00:20:58,557 --> 00:21:00,457
What's wrong with him?

254
00:21:00,525 --> 00:21:02,550
He's drunk.

255
00:21:02,694 --> 00:21:05,162
- Is he annoyed with us?
- No.

256
00:21:05,297 --> 00:21:06,662
You sure?

257
00:21:11,036 --> 00:21:12,970
She doesn't look too happy.

258
00:21:14,139 --> 00:21:16,164
Didn't you have to get up early?

259
00:21:18,377 --> 00:21:20,845
I'm doing too much
foryou tonight.

260
00:21:21,079 --> 00:21:24,014
- Maybe it means something.
- Yeah. That you've got a nerve.

261
00:21:24,082 --> 00:21:26,016
It's just for a minute.

262
00:21:26,084 --> 00:21:28,780
Long enough for my friend Nuria
to admit defeat.

263
00:21:28,887 --> 00:21:31,355
This is my place.

264
00:21:31,423 --> 00:21:34,654
- Don't dare laugh at it.
- Why would I laugh?

265
00:21:34,760 --> 00:21:37,661
It's nothing special,
but it's cheap.

266
00:21:42,434 --> 00:21:45,528
- Do you like clowns?
- They're not clowns.

267
00:21:45,604 --> 00:21:47,970
They're mime artists.

268
00:21:48,073 --> 00:21:49,438
Pancho!

269
00:21:50,609 --> 00:21:53,703
- I've got a cat.
- I hate cats.

270
00:21:53,779 --> 00:21:56,748
They're almost as false
as actresses.

271
00:21:56,815 --> 00:21:58,908
Says the caterer.

272
00:21:59,785 --> 00:22:02,151
How do you pay for this?

273
00:22:02,220 --> 00:22:05,815
Do your parents help?
Do you work?

274
00:22:05,924 --> 00:22:08,586
He's real nosy,
isn't he, Pancho?

275
00:22:08,727 --> 00:22:10,627
I'm an arms dealer.

276
00:22:10,729 --> 00:22:15,029
Fancy that! I always wanted to know
how arms dealers lived.

277
00:22:15,133 --> 00:22:17,067
Now you do.

278
00:22:40,058 --> 00:22:42,288
How can I explain it to you?

279
00:22:43,295 --> 00:22:47,026
You wouldn't understand.
Even I don't understand.

280
00:22:47,165 --> 00:22:51,727
She was making coffee
and I started snooping around.

281
00:22:51,837 --> 00:22:55,705
Suddenly, I got this stupid feeling
a lot ofpeople get.

282
00:22:55,807 --> 00:22:57,468
Wel l, I I i ke it.

283
00:22:57,542 --> 00:22:59,945
- What didyou feel?
- That I loved her.

284
00:22:59,945 --> 00:23:03,346
- God, I'm even embarrassed to say it.
- I d id n't hear you.

285
00:23:04,616 --> 00:23:06,516
I said I like your place.

286
00:23:06,618 --> 00:23:09,985
And I like yours.
Let's swap.

287
00:23:10,088 --> 00:23:12,716
You wouldn't like it
tomorrow morning.

288
00:23:12,824 --> 00:23:15,793
I said it because of the decor.

289
00:23:15,927 --> 00:23:18,725
Your place is more personal.

290
00:23:18,830 --> 00:23:21,390
- And warmer.
- Warmer?

291
00:23:21,500 --> 00:23:23,934
- Yes.
- You think my house is cold?

292
00:23:24,002 --> 00:23:26,197
- A bit.
- And am I?

293
00:23:26,304 --> 00:23:29,000
- I don't know.
- You said my house seemed cold.

294
00:23:30,041 --> 00:23:33,135
Ifyou're waiting for me
to list your virtues, hard luck.

295
00:23:34,346 --> 00:23:36,541
You thinkyou're real smart.

296
00:23:36,648 --> 00:23:38,513
- Maybe.
- Well, you're wrong.

297
00:23:38,650 --> 00:23:41,016
I don't need you
to list my virtues.

298
00:23:41,119 --> 00:23:43,417
No, I'm sure you know
what they are.

299
00:23:43,522 --> 00:23:46,923
- But you'd like me to see them, too.
- So you say.

300
00:23:47,025 --> 00:23:48,993
I'm not going
to argue about it.

301
00:23:49,127 --> 00:23:53,393
- Just as well. You'd lose.
- Oh, yeah?

302
00:23:53,532 --> 00:23:57,730
But I don't want to argue either.
I propose we do the opposite.

303
00:23:57,836 --> 00:24:00,270
- We don't argue?
- We show our defects.

304
00:24:02,007 --> 00:24:03,406
Great!

305
00:24:16,488 --> 00:24:18,388
I hope you're being fair.

306
00:24:18,490 --> 00:24:20,651
This is absolutely you.

307
00:24:23,728 --> 00:24:26,162
Well, mine is finished.

308
00:24:31,069 --> 00:24:34,038
Fuck!
That's how you see me?

309
00:24:36,575 --> 00:24:39,305
- Did I go too far?
- Sign it.

310
00:24:43,582 --> 00:24:46,642
Let's see mine.

311
00:24:47,752 --> 00:24:49,185
It's lovely!

312
00:24:50,956 --> 00:24:53,789
- It's not a caricature.
- You see.

313
00:24:53,925 --> 00:24:55,358
You draw beautifully.

314
00:24:55,427 --> 00:24:58,021
- I'll sell it to you.
- Miser. How much?

315
00:24:58,096 --> 00:25:00,462
As it's you,
I'll sell it for...

316
00:25:01,566 --> 00:25:02,931
a kiss.

317
00:25:08,707 --> 00:25:11,540
That smile's going to kill me!

318
00:25:15,847 --> 00:25:18,577
It would be wrong
ifwe did anything tonight.

319
00:25:19,518 --> 00:25:21,713
- Why?
- Pelayo. Remember?

320
00:25:22,587 --> 00:25:24,020
Your best friend.

321
00:25:25,357 --> 00:25:29,020
He doesn't have to find out.
Besides, he'd do the same.

322
00:25:30,495 --> 00:25:32,622
I see friendship
really matters to you.

323
00:25:32,764 --> 00:25:36,131
It does. That's why
I wouldn't tell him.

324
00:25:45,010 --> 00:25:46,500
Some people...

325
00:25:46,611 --> 00:25:50,809
say that they would be happy
with a normal life span.

326
00:25:50,916 --> 00:25:54,181
But "normal" means different things,
depending on--

327
00:25:54,286 --> 00:25:56,447
What are you looking at?

328
00:25:56,521 --> 00:25:58,421
I'm watching TV.

329
00:25:58,490 --> 00:26:02,358
The Romans, for instance,
lived only 25 years.

330
00:26:02,460 --> 00:26:03,893
Today...

331
00:26:03,929 --> 00:26:06,397
that figure has tripled,
which means that--

332
00:26:06,464 --> 00:26:11,401
- What the fuck is he on about?
- I saw this before.

333
00:26:11,503 --> 00:26:13,437
It's about cryonization.

334
00:26:13,505 --> 00:26:15,302
Cryo what?

335
00:26:15,407 --> 00:26:17,773
When they freeze you
or something.

336
00:26:19,444 --> 00:26:20,809
Like Walt Disney.

337
00:26:21,646 --> 00:26:23,580
Wow, that's cold!

338
00:26:24,583 --> 00:26:26,050
Hey, you!

339
00:26:26,151 --> 00:26:27,812
There won't be a landslide.

340
00:26:27,919 --> 00:26:32,219
It isn't dangerous. The ground
is firm here and very solid.

341
00:26:35,126 --> 00:26:38,323
- Are you leaving?
- I'm going home. Here's my number.

342
00:26:39,531 --> 00:26:42,056
But I'll call tomorrow.

343
00:26:42,200 --> 00:26:43,667
What for?

344
00:26:46,638 --> 00:26:49,300
All right, I won't call.

345
00:26:49,374 --> 00:26:53,037
- Cesar?
- What is it?

346
00:26:53,144 --> 00:26:56,443
Come here.
I want to tell you a secret.

347
00:27:06,658 --> 00:27:08,057
Come here.

348
00:27:44,195 --> 00:27:45,719
Hello, darling.

349
00:27:47,098 --> 00:27:48,656
Did you follow me?

350
00:27:48,767 --> 00:27:50,997
Of course I didn't.

351
00:27:51,102 --> 00:27:54,128
But I had the feeling
we'd meet.

352
00:27:54,272 --> 00:27:57,036
- How was the brunette?
- Good. Why?

353
00:27:57,108 --> 00:28:00,703
From your face, I'd say
you didn't sleep with her.

354
00:28:00,812 --> 00:28:04,646
Let me guess. You didn't sleep
with her, but you don't mind.

355
00:28:05,483 --> 00:28:08,509
You have all the time
in the world for that.

356
00:28:08,653 --> 00:28:11,053
And I bet you're
seeing her tomorrow.

357
00:28:11,156 --> 00:28:13,920
- Brilliant.
- Aren't I? There's more.

358
00:28:14,025 --> 00:28:16,323
- Well?
- I scored at the party, too.

359
00:28:16,428 --> 00:28:19,761
But he wasn't up for it,
so I'm still hot for it.

360
00:28:19,864 --> 00:28:22,833
- And?
- And until you meet up again...

361
00:28:22,934 --> 00:28:25,698
with your Miss Universe,
you could have fun.

362
00:28:27,539 --> 00:28:30,007
No. I think I prefer
to go home and sleep.

363
00:28:30,108 --> 00:28:33,236
Come on, Cesar.
It's your birthday.

364
00:28:37,282 --> 00:28:39,876
- Skip it. I'm going home.
- What's up, Cesar?

365
00:28:39,951 --> 00:28:41,441
Are you scared?

366
00:29:22,160 --> 00:29:25,391
- Want some of this?
- No, thanks.

367
00:29:25,497 --> 00:29:27,488
Sure, act innocent now.

368
00:29:27,632 --> 00:29:30,123
I don't need that
to enjoy myself.

369
00:29:30,268 --> 00:29:31,895
I see that.

370
00:29:32,804 --> 00:29:34,294
That's not a good idea.

371
00:29:39,110 --> 00:29:40,475
Do what you want.

372
00:29:44,482 --> 00:29:46,507
What's happiness for you?

373
00:29:47,685 --> 00:29:49,880
- What?
- For me, this is happiness.

374
00:29:49,988 --> 00:29:53,389
Being here with you.
What about you?

375
00:29:53,491 --> 00:29:57,518
I can't handle heavy conversations
right now.

376
00:29:59,197 --> 00:30:03,065
Your thoughts are
somewhere else, right?

377
00:30:03,168 --> 00:30:04,658
Maybe.

378
00:30:13,077 --> 00:30:14,977
One thing really bothers me.

379
00:30:15,847 --> 00:30:19,840
- What?
- You know nothing about me.

380
00:30:19,918 --> 00:30:22,216
Except my name's Nuria
and I'm a good fuck.

381
00:30:22,287 --> 00:30:23,914
Two important things.

382
00:30:24,022 --> 00:30:26,388
You don't know my address
or telephone number.

383
00:30:27,926 --> 00:30:31,794
We have to start somewhere.
I'm going to see your house now.

384
00:30:33,598 --> 00:30:34,997
It's not far.

385
00:30:44,976 --> 00:30:46,910
Tell me something.

386
00:30:46,978 --> 00:30:49,572
Do you believe in God?

387
00:31:51,175 --> 00:31:53,166
- Hello.
- Hello.

388
00:31:55,513 --> 00:31:57,913
- How are you?
- You got home all right?

389
00:31:58,016 --> 00:32:01,474
Yeah. Well, I had
a horrible dream.

390
00:32:01,586 --> 00:32:03,918
That you never saw me again.

391
00:32:03,988 --> 00:32:07,185
Yes. I came out ofyour house,
go to my car...

392
00:32:07,292 --> 00:32:09,556
and that crazy bitch
has been following me.

393
00:32:09,694 --> 00:32:11,753
- Who, that Nuria?
- Yes.

394
00:32:11,863 --> 00:32:13,797
She comes over and says,
"Want a lift? "

395
00:32:13,865 --> 00:32:16,425
She goes on so much
I don't know how to say no.

396
00:32:16,534 --> 00:32:20,026
So I get in the car,
she drives faster and faster...

397
00:32:20,171 --> 00:32:22,071
and kills herself.

398
00:32:22,173 --> 00:32:24,038
- With me inside.
- That's horrible.

399
00:32:24,175 --> 00:32:25,642
But the worst part...

400
00:32:25,710 --> 00:32:28,702
is that my face
is completely destroyed...

401
00:32:28,813 --> 00:32:31,611
Iike "The Phantom of the Opera."

402
00:32:31,716 --> 00:32:34,412
I couldn't wake up.

403
00:32:34,519 --> 00:32:36,384
I was a monster.

404
00:32:37,388 --> 00:32:40,050
You're a monster anyway.

405
00:32:40,158 --> 00:32:43,992
- Oh, yeah?
- Yeah. I'm a monster, too.

406
00:32:44,062 --> 00:32:45,927
Look.

407
00:32:49,701 --> 00:32:51,566
How was your house?

408
00:32:52,637 --> 00:32:54,571
Was anyone left?

409
00:32:55,440 --> 00:32:56,873
Left where?

410
00:32:56,941 --> 00:33:00,206
In your house.
There was a party, remember?

411
00:33:01,512 --> 00:33:03,275
A party?

412
00:33:09,554 --> 00:33:11,488
Dreaming is shit.

413
00:33:12,857 --> 00:33:15,291
Unless the dream was nice.

414
00:33:15,393 --> 00:33:18,590
In the park, children playing,
a girl who lovesyou.

415
00:33:18,730 --> 00:33:20,322
That's why.

416
00:33:20,431 --> 00:33:23,195
Then you wake up
andyou want to die.

417
00:33:32,210 --> 00:33:36,306
At first, I didn 't even have
the strength to react.

418
00:33:36,414 --> 00:33:38,814
I'd been in a coma
for three weeks.

419
00:33:38,916 --> 00:33:40,543
You were lucky.

420
00:33:40,618 --> 00:33:42,813
You could've died
like Nuria.

421
00:33:42,920 --> 00:33:46,287
And what?
I would've been better off.

422
00:33:46,391 --> 00:33:48,382
Didyou see her body?

423
00:33:48,459 --> 00:33:51,223
- I never d id.
- You think she didn't die?

424
00:33:52,363 --> 00:33:53,830
I'm like you.

425
00:33:53,965 --> 00:33:56,957
I only believe what I see.

426
00:33:58,369 --> 00:34:01,202
Cesar, show me your face,
please.

427
00:34:01,272 --> 00:34:02,762
- What for?
- Look.

428
00:34:02,874 --> 00:34:05,502
It's true you had an accident.
It's true...

429
00:34:05,610 --> 00:34:07,703
that you were disfigured,
but not anymore.

430
00:34:07,779 --> 00:34:10,213
Take that off.
The doctors fixed you.

431
00:34:10,281 --> 00:34:12,545
They didn't have
a fucking clue!

432
00:34:12,617 --> 00:34:16,246
In the accident, you didn't lose
just skin and some muscle.

433
00:34:16,320 --> 00:34:20,450
The blow was so severe it caused
a multiple fracture of the skull.

434
00:34:20,558 --> 00:34:23,493
We secured the osseous structure
with metal wires...

435
00:34:23,628 --> 00:34:26,688
and over that,
we reinserted the muscles...

436
00:34:26,831 --> 00:34:28,731
we could still retrieve.

437
00:34:28,833 --> 00:34:31,301
Yes, very nice,
but I know all that.

438
00:34:31,369 --> 00:34:33,929
I've had it explained to me
1 50 times.

439
00:34:34,038 --> 00:34:36,006
But you never say
when you'll operate.

440
00:34:36,107 --> 00:34:40,373
- I've been waiting two months.
- But we've operated three times.

441
00:34:40,478 --> 00:34:43,811
I wouldn't call that
an operation. I'd call it--

442
00:34:43,881 --> 00:34:47,840
Well, I don't know
what you'd call it.

443
00:34:47,952 --> 00:34:50,079
The symmetry isn't perfect...

444
00:34:50,188 --> 00:34:53,749
but what we've done with your face is,
if I may say so...

445
00:34:53,891 --> 00:34:55,381
a craftsman's job.

446
00:34:55,493 --> 00:34:57,757
We can't work on skin
which is pure scars.

447
00:34:57,895 --> 00:35:00,056
No, no, there must be some way.

448
00:35:00,164 --> 00:35:01,597
- What?
- "What? "

449
00:35:01,666 --> 00:35:03,827
You're the doctors, aren't you?

450
00:35:05,169 --> 00:35:07,069
A transplant, whatever!

451
00:35:07,171 --> 00:35:10,538
There's a problem with fibrosis,
ifwe operate again...

452
00:35:10,641 --> 00:35:12,666
we may just cause
further damage.

453
00:35:12,777 --> 00:35:15,302
We'd need
millimetric precision...

454
00:35:15,379 --> 00:35:17,404
and as of today
it's impossible.

455
00:35:18,616 --> 00:35:21,949
Let's look at this.
I'm not an idiot.

456
00:35:22,019 --> 00:35:24,385
Today, people change
their breasts.

457
00:35:24,489 --> 00:35:26,514
They have hair implants.

458
00:35:26,657 --> 00:35:29,649
They even change the color
of their skin.

459
00:35:29,727 --> 00:35:32,389
Are you saying that on
the threshold of the year 2000...

460
00:35:32,530 --> 00:35:37,763
you can't do a simple operation
and sort out this fuck-up?

461
00:35:37,869 --> 00:35:41,305
- It isn't so simple, Cesar. Remember--
- Don't patronize me!

462
00:35:41,405 --> 00:35:43,305
Stop treating me like a child!

463
00:35:46,544 --> 00:35:48,944
I'm not just any patient.

464
00:35:49,046 --> 00:35:51,412
And this isn't a welfare hospital.

465
00:35:53,684 --> 00:35:56,152
I'm willing to pay any amount.

466
00:35:59,590 --> 00:36:00,921
You're in charge.

467
00:36:02,193 --> 00:36:04,491
They say you're the best
in your field.

468
00:36:04,595 --> 00:36:07,564
Well, invent something.
Experiment with me.

469
00:36:07,698 --> 00:36:10,667
I've seen patients
who've lost all their features...

470
00:36:10,735 --> 00:36:12,600
who can't even talk.

471
00:36:12,703 --> 00:36:15,672
At least you can lookyourself
in the eyes.

472
00:36:15,740 --> 00:36:18,231
What good is that?

473
00:36:18,342 --> 00:36:20,936
Every time I look in the mirror,
I want to die.

474
00:36:21,045 --> 00:36:23,172
Your case isn't so serious.

475
00:36:23,247 --> 00:36:25,147
Just learn to accept it.

476
00:36:25,249 --> 00:36:27,615
And who will accept me?

477
00:36:27,718 --> 00:36:30,983
Will you explain to the people
who look at me in the street?

478
00:36:32,523 --> 00:36:35,390
Will you tell them
that looks aren't important?

479
00:36:35,459 --> 00:36:37,859
That beauty is on the inside?

480
00:36:43,801 --> 00:36:46,895
We'd like to show you something.

481
00:37:05,089 --> 00:37:06,522
What is this?

482
00:37:06,591 --> 00:37:09,253
A facial prosthesis.

483
00:37:09,360 --> 00:37:12,488
We use it in extreme cases
of rejection like yours.

484
00:37:21,772 --> 00:37:23,171
This is shit!

485
00:37:23,274 --> 00:37:25,708
It's not the best solution...

486
00:37:25,810 --> 00:37:28,142
but it's all we can do
for the moment.

487
00:37:28,246 --> 00:37:31,215
I want a face!
Not a mask!

488
00:37:33,184 --> 00:37:35,311
I don't work miracles.

489
00:37:35,486 --> 00:37:38,751
That's what the bastard said.

490
00:37:38,823 --> 00:37:41,155
But in the end, they did.

491
00:37:42,126 --> 00:37:43,616
Did what?

492
00:37:43,728 --> 00:37:45,127
Work a miracle.

493
00:37:46,130 --> 00:37:47,563
So it seems.

494
00:37:47,665 --> 00:37:50,429
So it seems?
Things are or they aren't?

495
00:37:50,534 --> 00:37:53,765
- Did they do it or not?
- I'm tired. Why don't you go?

496
00:37:58,476 --> 00:38:00,706
I'll be back on Tuesday.
Want anything?

497
00:38:00,811 --> 00:38:03,678
- No.
- All right. See you on Tuesday.

498
00:38:03,781 --> 00:38:05,749
A pad and a pencil.

499
00:38:05,816 --> 00:38:08,376
But don't tell them.
I don't want to owe them anything.

500
00:41:46,670 --> 00:41:48,763
Have I changed so much?

501
00:41:48,839 --> 00:41:50,773
Because I recognize you.

502
00:41:56,847 --> 00:41:58,246
How are you?

503
00:41:58,349 --> 00:42:00,146
"How are you? "

504
00:42:00,251 --> 00:42:05,553
You're playing a part now, but I don't
know what. Your lips are smiling.

505
00:42:05,623 --> 00:42:07,488
- But your eyes are trembling.
- What?

506
00:42:07,591 --> 00:42:10,958
You're really very good
as an actress.

507
00:42:11,061 --> 00:42:14,497
I asked you how you were.
You didn't answer.

508
00:42:14,565 --> 00:42:18,126
I'm alive.
How should I be?

509
00:42:18,269 --> 00:42:19,998
And I'm tired.

510
00:42:20,137 --> 00:42:24,437
Tired ofwaiting foryou to call,
even to say "Tough luck."

511
00:42:24,508 --> 00:42:27,102
- I was busy.
- Bullshit!

512
00:42:29,980 --> 00:42:32,642
I was afraid you'd feel uncomfortable
if I rang.

513
00:42:34,985 --> 00:42:38,182
You were afraid
you'd feel uncomfortable.

514
00:42:38,289 --> 00:42:42,248
Afraid you couldn't
look me in the face, like now.

515
00:42:53,571 --> 00:42:55,471
That's not true.

516
00:43:12,823 --> 00:43:14,723
I've often dreamed
of this moment.

517
00:43:14,858 --> 00:43:16,223
What moment?

518
00:43:20,197 --> 00:43:23,166
The moment we'd meet again.

519
00:43:23,233 --> 00:43:26,134
In my dream,
we were just like this.

520
00:43:26,236 --> 00:43:28,704
Here, in the park.

521
00:43:29,807 --> 00:43:32,776
Although something was different.

522
00:43:35,045 --> 00:43:37,206
What?

523
00:43:40,684 --> 00:43:43,346
It wasn't raining.

524
00:43:46,090 --> 00:43:47,682
I have to go, Cesar.

525
00:43:47,791 --> 00:43:51,784
- What are you doing tomorrow night?
- Studying. I'm very busy.

526
00:43:51,929 --> 00:43:54,898
- It's Friday. We could meet.
- I've got a lot to do.

527
00:43:54,965 --> 00:43:57,126
All right, so long.

528
00:43:59,403 --> 00:44:00,893
Cesar!

529
00:44:03,407 --> 00:44:05,534
We'll meet ifyou want.

530
00:44:06,744 --> 00:44:08,177
Ifyou want.

531
00:44:10,280 --> 00:44:13,511
As soon as there is
the slightest possibility ofdeath...

532
00:44:13,584 --> 00:44:16,610
the stabilization and transport team
goes into action.

533
00:44:16,720 --> 00:44:18,915
Once the client is declared
legally dead...

534
00:44:19,023 --> 00:44:21,958
he is put into
a maintenance capsule...

535
00:44:22,059 --> 00:44:25,426
and the transport legalities
are sorted out.

536
00:44:25,529 --> 00:44:28,089
In the storeroom in Arizona
in the U.S.A...

537
00:44:28,232 --> 00:44:31,963
a team ofspecialists prepare the body
for final freezing.

538
00:44:32,936 --> 00:44:34,631
Among other measures...

539
00:44:34,705 --> 00:44:39,039
blood is replaced by a solution
which preserves the organs.

540
00:44:40,944 --> 00:44:42,172
Finally...

541
00:44:42,279 --> 00:44:44,543
the client is put
in the capsule....

542
00:44:44,648 --> 00:44:47,776
where he will remain
until medicine can reenergize him.

543
00:44:52,790 --> 00:44:54,917
To be honest,
I'd have to think it over.

544
00:44:54,992 --> 00:44:57,586
It's hard to accept the idea.

545
00:44:57,695 --> 00:45:00,027
How should we view it?

546
00:45:00,097 --> 00:45:04,625
We are, undoubtedly,
facing a major development...

547
00:45:04,768 --> 00:45:07,703
a new challenge for humanity.

548
00:45:07,805 --> 00:45:11,206
It's understandable that
the first reaction is rejection.

549
00:45:11,308 --> 00:45:14,300
We have now got the means
to do it.

550
00:45:14,378 --> 00:45:16,710
We've got the technology.

551
00:45:16,814 --> 00:45:20,306
But, above all, we have
sufficient moral maturity...

552
00:45:20,417 --> 00:45:23,352
to understand what
this new step means...

553
00:45:23,454 --> 00:45:26,355
for human evolution,
to look at the future...

554
00:45:26,457 --> 00:45:29,551
and put an end to certain
meaningless taboos...

555
00:45:29,693 --> 00:45:32,184
inherited from ancient religions...

556
00:45:32,329 --> 00:45:35,025
old and useless memories.

557
00:45:35,165 --> 00:45:37,633
Thankyou for speaking to us.

558
00:45:37,701 --> 00:45:39,498
And thankyou
to our audience--

559
00:46:06,630 --> 00:46:08,154
- Hi.
- Hi.

560
00:46:08,265 --> 00:46:11,701
- What's that?
- Shit, isn't it?

561
00:46:11,802 --> 00:46:14,635
But they suggested I wear it
in case of infection.

562
00:46:17,875 --> 00:46:21,333
Well, kid, what're you up to?

563
00:46:21,478 --> 00:46:23,605
Arguing with doctors all day.

564
00:46:23,714 --> 00:46:25,739
- You should go out more.
- I'm trying.

565
00:46:25,849 --> 00:46:28,909
- What're you having?
- Rum and Coke. You want one?

566
00:46:29,019 --> 00:46:31,920
- Yes.
- I'll get you one.

567
00:46:32,022 --> 00:46:34,081
I'm going to the bathroom.

568
00:46:36,393 --> 00:46:39,123
- Take that off.
- Why?

569
00:46:39,229 --> 00:46:42,630
Don't you realize you won't
be able to hide your face?

570
00:46:43,600 --> 00:46:45,966
I told you,
it's to stop infections.

571
00:46:46,069 --> 00:46:47,536
Sure.

572
00:46:47,604 --> 00:46:51,199
Ifyou're embarrassed, just go.
Nobody asked you to come.

573
00:46:51,275 --> 00:46:53,368
- Sofia did.
- What?

574
00:46:54,678 --> 00:46:57,670
- She didn't want to be alone with you.
- Why not?

575
00:46:57,781 --> 00:47:01,148
- You're giving her a hard time.
- I'm having a hard time.

576
00:47:01,218 --> 00:47:03,379
Talk to a psychologist,
or to me.

577
00:47:03,487 --> 00:47:06,047
Don't take it out on a girl
you met once.

578
00:47:06,156 --> 00:47:07,919
Did she say that?

579
00:47:09,159 --> 00:47:11,127
Did she say that?

580
00:47:12,229 --> 00:47:14,959
- Bitch!
- Come back!

581
00:47:23,240 --> 00:47:24,867
Whiskey and Coke.

582
00:47:24,942 --> 00:47:28,173
- What whiskey?
- What did you say?

583
00:47:30,447 --> 00:47:33,280
What whiskey?

584
00:47:33,350 --> 00:47:35,875
Why don't you ask me
to my face, son of a bitch?

585
00:47:41,625 --> 00:47:43,024
Ballantine's.

586
00:48:05,582 --> 00:48:08,483
- Same again.
- No, this one's on me.

587
00:48:10,387 --> 00:48:14,585
- Why?
-Just is.

588
00:48:51,194 --> 00:48:53,822
Fix your face, man!

589
00:50:40,604 --> 00:50:43,402
- Hello.
- Hello.

590
00:50:43,507 --> 00:50:47,466
- Where were you?
- Around.

591
00:50:47,544 --> 00:50:49,478
Pelayo went to look foryou.

592
00:50:50,947 --> 00:50:53,415
And I came to look foryou.

593
00:50:53,517 --> 00:50:54,950
Why?

594
00:50:55,052 --> 00:50:56,986
To-- No reason.

595
00:50:58,155 --> 00:51:00,953
To buy you a drink.

596
00:51:02,793 --> 00:51:05,660
- Want a drink?
- No, thanks.

597
00:51:08,698 --> 00:51:11,428
Can you tell I'm elbowing in?

598
00:51:11,535 --> 00:51:14,902
The thing is,
I've got a problem.

599
00:51:15,005 --> 00:51:19,908
A girl's chasing me, and I need
some help to get rid ofher.

600
00:51:20,010 --> 00:51:22,877
Shit, shit, shit!
She's coming this way.

601
00:51:22,979 --> 00:51:26,437
She's coming this way.
Don't look. Don't look.

602
00:51:28,552 --> 00:51:31,578
You carry on talking,
act as if he weren't here.

603
00:51:31,688 --> 00:51:33,588
I mean, as if I were here.

604
00:51:33,690 --> 00:51:35,783
Keep talking.
Tra-la-lee, tra-la-la.

605
00:51:35,926 --> 00:51:39,362
What a lovely conversation
we're having.

606
00:51:43,266 --> 00:51:45,598
So that's it, here we are...

607
00:51:45,702 --> 00:51:48,432
having a bit of a chat
about life.

608
00:51:48,505 --> 00:51:49,904
That's enough!

609
00:52:00,484 --> 00:52:02,349
Where the hell were you?

610
00:52:04,621 --> 00:52:06,020
Around.

611
00:52:06,723 --> 00:52:08,884
I'm leaving. I'm tired.

612
00:52:08,959 --> 00:52:12,326
You two stay ifyou want.

613
00:52:18,902 --> 00:52:22,099
Well, this is where
I leave you.

614
00:52:22,205 --> 00:52:24,935
- I'll see you home.
- No, I live very close.

615
00:52:25,041 --> 00:52:27,009
- I've got the motorbike.
- No.

616
00:52:27,110 --> 00:52:29,704
- Don't be silly.
- Lay off, Pelayo.

617
00:52:29,779 --> 00:52:31,770
She wants to go on her own.

618
00:52:31,848 --> 00:52:34,112
Shut up. You're drunk.

619
00:52:34,184 --> 00:52:37,950
I might be drunk,
but I'm not an idiot.

620
00:52:38,054 --> 00:52:41,455
- Anyway, I'm not drunk.
- Really, you needn't bother.

621
00:52:41,525 --> 00:52:44,688
- As you wish.
- You're the one who's drunk.

622
00:52:44,828 --> 00:52:47,661
We'll call you to meet
some other day.

623
00:52:47,764 --> 00:52:49,891
All right. We could go
to the movies.

624
00:52:50,000 --> 00:52:51,900
- You hear?
- Great!

625
00:52:52,002 --> 00:52:54,095
Well, that's it, then.

626
00:52:56,640 --> 00:53:00,872
No, don't kiss me. You might
get poisoned by my drunken breath.

627
00:53:00,944 --> 00:53:05,108
Well, we'll meet up soon.

628
00:53:05,215 --> 00:53:06,580
Sure.

629
00:53:07,717 --> 00:53:09,582
We'll meet up soon.

630
00:53:24,234 --> 00:53:26,134
It's not cold.

631
00:53:33,810 --> 00:53:35,209
Well...

632
00:53:37,681 --> 00:53:40,616
I'm gonna have to go.

633
00:53:40,684 --> 00:53:42,675
Where are you going?

634
00:53:42,752 --> 00:53:45,118
I've just remembered
my bike is back there.

635
00:53:45,188 --> 00:53:49,249
- I'll go with you.
- No. Why? You're almost home now.

636
00:53:49,359 --> 00:53:52,260
- See you tomorrow.
- Pelayo, wait a minute.

637
00:53:54,231 --> 00:53:55,459
What?

638
00:54:02,272 --> 00:54:03,705
I don't know.

639
00:54:04,674 --> 00:54:08,041
You drank too much.
We'll talk tomorrow ifyou want.

640
00:54:08,144 --> 00:54:11,170
- Tomorrow I'll wish I were dead.
- You won't.

641
00:54:11,281 --> 00:54:13,272
You just need to rest.

642
00:54:14,351 --> 00:54:15,750
Pelayo!

643
00:54:20,857 --> 00:54:22,722
You're my best friend.

644
00:54:44,080 --> 00:54:45,980
Son of a bitch!

645
00:56:09,632 --> 00:56:10,826
Open your eyes.

646
00:56:18,108 --> 00:56:19,507
Cesar.

647
00:56:28,618 --> 00:56:30,017
It's me.

648
00:56:34,257 --> 00:56:35,588
Sofia!

649
00:56:37,093 --> 00:56:39,653
- What are you doing here?
- Forgive me.

650
00:56:39,763 --> 00:56:41,025
Why?

651
00:56:58,047 --> 00:56:59,912
I love you.

652
00:57:06,556 --> 00:57:07,955
Come on.

653
00:57:11,694 --> 00:57:15,186
- What's wrong?
- Nothing.

654
00:57:15,331 --> 00:57:18,300
I still can't believe
this is really happening.

655
00:57:21,037 --> 00:57:22,527
Where's Pelayo?

656
00:57:22,639 --> 00:57:25,574
I don't know.
He went with you, didn't he?

657
00:57:25,675 --> 00:57:27,472
Yes.

658
00:57:27,544 --> 00:57:28,977
Of course.

659
00:57:33,716 --> 00:57:35,115
Come on.

660
00:58:00,376 --> 00:58:02,344
God, what a sensation!

661
00:58:03,446 --> 00:58:05,038
Ofwhat?

662
00:58:05,148 --> 00:58:08,879
Do you ever feel
you've lived something before?

663
00:58:08,952 --> 00:58:10,886
Yes.

664
00:58:10,954 --> 00:58:13,388
Why is that?

665
00:58:13,490 --> 00:58:15,856
They say it's a lapse
in the brain.

666
00:58:16,860 --> 00:58:19,124
I've been here before.

667
00:58:21,064 --> 00:58:23,965
It usually goes away
after a few seconds.

668
00:58:25,835 --> 00:58:28,235
I don't want it to go away.

669
00:58:41,718 --> 00:58:43,583
You've made use ofyour time.

670
00:58:45,188 --> 00:58:47,247
That's all there is here.

671
00:58:50,126 --> 00:58:52,822
Very pretty. Is it Sofia?

672
00:59:02,605 --> 00:59:05,267
How much longer will I be here?

673
00:59:05,375 --> 00:59:07,502
No one ever knows that.

674
00:59:07,577 --> 00:59:10,478
Even my worst nightmare
was never like this place.

675
00:59:10,547 --> 00:59:14,347
It's a psychiatric penitentiary.
No more, no less.

676
00:59:17,453 --> 00:59:20,854
- I shouldn't be here.
- You're accused of murder.

677
00:59:20,924 --> 00:59:23,893
- I don't even know what I did.
- Tell me something.

678
00:59:23,993 --> 00:59:29,192
-Does the name Eli mean anything to you?
-Eli?

679
00:59:29,299 --> 00:59:31,563
You know a girl with that name?

680
00:59:31,634 --> 00:59:34,398
No. Why do you ask?

681
00:59:34,470 --> 00:59:37,405
It seems you kept
repeating it last night.

682
00:59:37,473 --> 00:59:40,169
I guess I was dreaming.

683
00:59:40,276 --> 00:59:43,575
- What did you dream?
- I can't remember.

684
00:59:43,646 --> 00:59:48,106
- It could be important.
- How could it be important?

685
00:59:48,217 --> 00:59:52,210
Look, I can prove you didn't know
what you were doing...

686
00:59:52,288 --> 00:59:55,257
but first I have to find
some explanation for all this.

687
00:59:55,325 --> 00:59:58,783
There is no explanation.
I told you the other day.

688
00:59:58,861 --> 01:00:00,351
What did you dream, Cesar?

689
01:00:03,199 --> 01:00:05,133
I don't know.

690
01:00:06,336 --> 01:00:08,668
I only remember bits.

691
01:00:11,207 --> 01:00:14,301
First, I'm in a kind of office.

692
01:00:14,410 --> 01:00:16,674
A secretary shows me
into another office.

693
01:00:17,847 --> 01:00:20,975
There's a photo
ofa sunset and a man.

694
01:00:22,051 --> 01:00:24,485
Then, I don't know.

695
01:00:24,554 --> 01:00:27,682
- They show me lots ofpapers.
- What papers?

696
01:00:27,790 --> 01:00:29,417
I don't know.

697
01:00:29,525 --> 01:00:32,119
But I sign them.

698
01:00:32,195 --> 01:00:35,096
Does the office belong
to your company?

699
01:00:35,231 --> 01:00:38,166
No, I don't recognize it.

700
01:00:38,234 --> 01:00:40,327
You dreamed of a place
you'd never been?

701
01:00:40,436 --> 01:00:44,133
Yes. That happens a lot,
doesn't it?

702
01:00:44,240 --> 01:00:47,403
Are they the papers
you signed with the doctors?

703
01:00:47,510 --> 01:00:51,310
No, what happened with the doctors
was surreal.

704
01:00:51,414 --> 01:00:54,906
- Why?
- They rang me to go to the hospital.

705
01:00:56,319 --> 01:00:59,811
When I arrived,
the whole surgical team was waiting.

706
01:00:59,922 --> 01:01:05,588
Formonths, those faces had looked at me
with indifference and impotence.

707
01:01:05,728 --> 01:01:08,253
Now they were all smiles.

708
01:01:08,398 --> 01:01:13,335
The same bastard who had said my case
was hopeless talked about an operation.

709
01:01:13,436 --> 01:01:17,702
They had a new revolutionary system
in the clinic now.

710
01:01:17,774 --> 01:01:22,370
They said that within two weeks my face
would be completely reconstructed.

711
01:01:22,478 --> 01:01:24,378
You didn 't believe them?

712
01:01:24,480 --> 01:01:30,316
Not at fi rst. I thought it was just
a way to get more money out of me.

713
01:01:30,420 --> 01:01:33,856
But they showed me
all the gad gets for the operation.

714
01:01:33,956 --> 01:01:37,187
It looked like science fiction.

715
01:01:37,260 --> 01:01:40,957
All I could see were cables,
switches, monitors.

716
01:01:41,097 --> 01:01:45,431
Actually, I never really knew
what they were going to do.

717
01:01:45,535 --> 01:01:47,526
But I thought I'd nothing to lose.

718
01:01:47,637 --> 01:01:50,606
Those people
were used to rhinoplasties...

719
01:01:50,673 --> 01:01:54,973
Iiposuctions, hair transplants,
but my operation was much more.

720
01:01:55,078 --> 01:01:57,308
In less than a week...

721
01:01:57,413 --> 01:02:00,246
my life had turned around.

722
01:02:00,349 --> 01:02:05,048
One night, I was lying
on the ground drunk, waiting to die.

723
01:02:05,154 --> 01:02:07,418
The next morning,
my dreams were coming true...

724
01:02:07,523 --> 01:02:09,855
I i ke i n the movies.

725
01:02:09,926 --> 01:02:13,919
Sofia loved me, and the doctors
found the miracle cure.

726
01:02:14,030 --> 01:02:17,796
I don't know.
Obviously, I was suspicious.

727
01:02:17,900 --> 01:02:19,629
Suspicious?

728
01:02:19,736 --> 01:02:23,103
Ofwhom? Ofwhat?

729
01:02:23,172 --> 01:02:25,106
I don't know.

730
01:02:26,309 --> 01:02:28,300
In life, you never know.

731
01:02:28,411 --> 01:02:30,936
Happiness comes
when you least expect it.

732
01:02:34,083 --> 01:02:36,483
I once knew a guy
who was alone in the world.

733
01:02:36,586 --> 01:02:39,419
Suddenly, he was married
with two daughters.

734
01:02:39,489 --> 01:02:43,152
Fuck, you've got
a strange idea of happiness.

735
01:02:52,034 --> 01:02:55,970
Well, that depends on the individual.
What's happiness foryou?

736
01:02:56,038 --> 01:02:58,006
What's happiness foryou?

737
01:03:00,476 --> 01:03:02,569
Don't ask any more stupid questions.

738
01:03:02,645 --> 01:03:06,046
But at that time, you were happy.
Or weren't you?

739
01:03:06,149 --> 01:03:09,482
So what?
My life now is shit.

740
01:03:09,585 --> 01:03:14,045
All I can do is eat, shit, sleep
and dream of my memories.

741
01:03:15,324 --> 01:03:17,622
It's good that you remember.

742
01:03:32,708 --> 01:03:36,109
- Well?
- Well, what?

743
01:03:36,212 --> 01:03:40,444
They were to remove
the plates today.

744
01:03:40,550 --> 01:03:43,519
- And they did.
- And?

745
01:03:43,586 --> 01:03:47,317
Well, my ears are where
they should be.

746
01:03:47,390 --> 01:03:49,620
Cesar, don't scare me.

747
01:03:51,527 --> 01:03:55,224
- Take off the plates.
- You can do it.

748
01:05:14,277 --> 01:05:16,507
How did they do it?

749
01:05:54,016 --> 01:05:58,646
Wait.Just to say
that I love you.

750
01:05:59,855 --> 01:06:02,915
You're going too fast...

751
01:06:02,992 --> 01:06:06,257
considering we met yesterday.

752
01:06:06,395 --> 01:06:07,453
Yesterday?

753
01:06:07,596 --> 01:06:10,531
My birthday, don't you remember?

754
01:06:11,834 --> 01:06:15,930
I met an incredible girl.
Her name was Sofia.

755
01:06:16,038 --> 01:06:19,667
But today I woke up feeling great...

756
01:06:19,775 --> 01:06:22,300
and now I'm with the girl again.

757
01:06:27,350 --> 01:06:29,215
