Tell me the truth!

968
01:22:08,456 --> 01:22:11,254
- I must know what you took.
- I didn't take anything!

969
01:22:11,326 --> 01:22:15,660
Don't you see? Your brain
could have been affected by the pills.

970
01:22:15,764 --> 01:22:17,925
- I didn't take any!
- You said you did!

971
01:22:18,033 --> 01:22:20,331
It's just a dream!

972
01:22:20,435 --> 01:22:22,426
Why make it more important
than it is?

973
01:22:22,537 --> 01:22:25,836
Can't you tell dreams from reality?
I can!

974
01:22:25,941 --> 01:22:29,274
Really? Don't make me laugh!

975
01:22:29,344 --> 01:22:32,279
Bodies that come to life,
people who disappear...

976
01:22:32,347 --> 01:22:34,372
you, the Phantom of the Opera!

977
01:22:39,020 --> 01:22:42,353
Tell me one thing. Do you remember
what you did to Sofia?

978
01:22:45,527 --> 01:22:46,960
It wasn't Sofia.

979
01:22:47,028 --> 01:22:51,192
I don't care who it was.
What did you do to her?

980
01:22:52,400 --> 01:22:54,197
You remember?

981
01:24:30,999 --> 01:24:32,432
My God!

982
01:24:36,504 --> 01:24:38,995
What are you doing?
I thought you were a burglar.

983
01:24:41,976 --> 01:24:43,603
Who are you?

984
01:24:43,711 --> 01:24:45,269
I'm Sofia.

985
01:24:46,147 --> 01:24:48,047
Sofia.

986
01:24:50,652 --> 01:24:52,847
You're not Sofia.

987
01:24:57,725 --> 01:25:00,091
Cesar, this will all
be over soon.

988
01:25:00,195 --> 01:25:02,095
We'll be together again.

989
01:25:03,465 --> 01:25:06,434
You'll forget Nuria
and I won't be afraid ofyou.

990
01:25:09,971 --> 01:25:13,099
- I'm thirsty.
- I'll get some water.

991
01:25:53,815 --> 01:25:55,077
Sofia!

992
01:25:56,885 --> 01:25:59,353
Yes, Cesar, I'm Sofia.

993
01:26:03,491 --> 01:26:05,152
I'm Sofia.

994
01:27:39,454 --> 01:27:42,014
I want to see you.

995
01:27:42,123 --> 01:27:45,251
I want to see you.
I want to see you!

996
01:27:50,164 --> 01:27:51,995
I want to see you!

997
01:29:35,002 --> 01:29:37,470
At times you dream
you're with someone.

998
01:29:37,672 --> 01:29:40,300
For example, your father.

999
01:29:40,408 --> 01:29:43,206
In seconds,
he becomes your mother...

1000
01:29:43,277 --> 01:29:47,179
and then, the news vendor
on the corner.

1001
01:29:47,248 --> 01:29:51,241
Yet you still feel as if
you're talking to the same person.

1002
01:29:52,520 --> 01:29:57,389
You thought you were at home, but
suddenly you realize you're in a school.

1003
01:29:57,458 --> 01:30:00,916
Or a hospital, or a prison.

1004
01:30:02,730 --> 01:30:05,198
Dreams are like that.

1005
01:30:05,299 --> 01:30:08,132
And at times the mind behaves
as if it were in a dream.

1006
01:30:08,236 --> 01:30:11,000
- You know what derangement is?
- For fuck's sake!

1007
01:30:11,139 --> 01:30:14,540
Say I'm stupid ifyou want,
but this isn't derangement!

1008
01:30:14,642 --> 01:30:16,633
Then what is it?

1009
01:30:16,744 --> 01:30:19,338
You tell me,
because I don't know.

1010
01:30:20,481 --> 01:30:23,450
I don't know what's in here,
or why you killed your girlfriend.

1011
01:30:23,518 --> 01:30:26,612
I don't know who Eli is,
or that man from the TV.

1012
01:30:26,721 --> 01:30:30,054
- I don't know anything.
- That makes two of us.

1013
01:30:41,736 --> 01:30:44,637
Will you still come
after the trial?

1014
01:30:44,705 --> 01:30:46,764
Don't you hate the sight of me?

1015
01:30:49,577 --> 01:30:52,705
- What will you plead?
- Why do you ask that?

1016
01:30:52,814 --> 01:30:55,749
The first hearing
is next week.

1017
01:30:59,821 --> 01:31:01,482
Temporary derangement.

1018
01:31:01,589 --> 01:31:04,387
It's your best chance.

1019
01:31:04,492 --> 01:31:06,483
Even so, it won't be much use.

1020
01:31:06,627 --> 01:31:09,095
They won't believe me.

1021
01:31:09,163 --> 01:31:11,097
Even I don't believe it.

1022
01:31:11,199 --> 01:31:12,598
What do you believe?

1023
01:31:14,202 --> 01:31:18,434
I thinkyou're very sick
and should stay here for a long time.

1024
01:31:20,074 --> 01:31:22,838
Don't worry.
I'll get at least 20 years.

1025
01:31:22,910 --> 01:31:26,004
Cesar, you may not believe it,
but I care about you.

1026
01:31:26,080 --> 01:31:28,605
I care a lot about you.

1027
01:31:30,618 --> 01:31:32,176
Look, kid.

1028
01:31:32,253 --> 01:31:35,848
Your case interests me.
I'm sorry about what's happened.

1029
01:31:35,957 --> 01:31:39,358
I even thought someone
was playing tricks on you, but...

1030
01:31:39,427 --> 01:31:41,918
I can't and mustn't
exceed my duties.

1031
01:31:41,996 --> 01:31:45,022
- I'm just a psychiatrist.
- You don't look like one.

1032
01:31:45,166 --> 01:31:47,726
- What do I look like?
- My father.

1033
01:31:47,835 --> 01:31:49,860
Preaching at me all day.

1034
01:31:49,937 --> 01:31:52,770
Your father's dead.

1035
01:31:52,874 --> 01:31:54,466
There you go.

1036
01:32:02,450 --> 01:32:06,614
By the way, what happened to that man
with the wife and two daughters?

1037
01:32:10,925 --> 01:32:12,893
I don't know.
I never saw him again.

1038
01:32:12,927 --> 01:32:14,895
Take my advice, get a lawyer.

1039
01:32:14,929 --> 01:32:17,056
Good-bye, Cesar.

1040
01:32:20,268 --> 01:32:21,895
Good-bye.

1041
01:32:21,969 --> 01:32:25,928
...the main Spanish investment,
but certainly the most novel.

1042
01:32:41,389 --> 01:32:43,880
...its economic presence in Cuba.

1043
01:32:43,958 --> 01:32:47,416
...depending on the era.

1044
01:32:47,528 --> 01:32:51,464
In the Roman Empire, for example,
the normal thing was to live...

1045
01:32:51,599 --> 01:32:53,567
only 25 years.

1046
01:33:00,041 --> 01:33:02,066
Who's got the remote?

1047
01:33:03,678 --> 01:33:05,737
Give it to me!

1048
01:33:12,653 --> 01:33:14,678
Get it off him!

1049
01:33:30,705 --> 01:33:32,570
What's up?

1050
01:33:32,673 --> 01:33:35,301
There's a computer here
connected to Internet.

1051
01:33:35,376 --> 01:33:38,277
They'll only let me use it
ifyou come with me.

1052
01:33:38,346 --> 01:33:41,804
- Why do you want Internet?
- I know what Eli is.

1053
01:33:41,882 --> 01:33:43,315
Wait!

1054
01:33:43,384 --> 01:33:46,285
Eli isn't a person,
it's a company.

1055
01:33:46,354 --> 01:33:48,686
- How do you know?
- It isn't Eli.

1056
01:33:48,789 --> 01:33:51,815
It's L.E. They're the initials
of an American company.

1057
01:33:51,959 --> 01:33:55,451
- What are you doing?
- Checking the "initials program."

1058
01:33:55,563 --> 01:33:58,157
It'll tell us all it knows
about L.E.

1059
01:34:03,037 --> 01:34:04,129
Shit!

1060
01:34:04,271 --> 01:34:07,365
- It'll take ages.
- No, wait.

1061
01:34:13,247 --> 01:34:14,942
Fuck!

1062
01:34:15,016 --> 01:34:17,280
I feel like
I've done this before.

1063
01:34:17,351 --> 01:34:20,013
A cerebral dysfunction.
A lapse in the brain.

1064
01:34:20,121 --> 01:34:22,612
No, not this time.

1065
01:34:22,690 --> 01:34:24,123
My God!

1066
01:34:24,191 --> 01:34:26,489
- That's it.
- The photo in your dream?

1067
01:34:26,627 --> 01:34:29,653
I had to see it before
I could dream about it, right?

1068
01:34:29,764 --> 01:34:30,992
"Cyronics."

1069
01:34:31,098 --> 01:34:33,123
- Cryonization.
- I'll print this.

1070
01:34:33,234 --> 01:34:37,364
Wait a minute. I don't see
what this has to do with your case.

1071
01:34:37,471 --> 01:34:40,872
The key is in here.
Look, there's an office in Madrid.

1072
01:34:40,941 --> 01:34:43,341
I'll go and check it out.

1073
01:34:43,411 --> 01:34:45,879
No! I have to go, too.

1074
01:34:45,946 --> 01:34:49,575
- I can't get you out of here.
- I'd be let out under supervision.

1075
01:34:49,684 --> 01:34:51,379
Make up some excuse.

1076
01:34:51,485 --> 01:34:53,214
- It isn't easy.
- You can do it.

1077
01:34:53,287 --> 01:34:55,881
You know something else,
don't you?

1078
01:34:58,793 --> 01:35:00,124
I don't know anything.

1079
01:35:00,194 --> 01:35:02,992
- I've just got a feeling.
- What is it?

1080
01:35:03,097 --> 01:35:05,895
I have to go there,
one way or another.

1081
01:35:49,977 --> 01:35:54,141
Let's get things straight.
We're outside, I'm armed.

1082
01:35:54,248 --> 01:35:56,808
My job is to stop you
doing anything stupid.

1083
01:35:56,917 --> 01:35:59,181
Try anything,
and you get a bullet.

1084
01:36:33,187 --> 01:36:35,417
I've been here before.

1085
01:36:35,489 --> 01:36:37,787
- This way.
- Move.

1086
01:36:52,973 --> 01:36:54,964
You've got 20 minutes.

1087
01:37:05,486 --> 01:37:07,852
It's just like in my dream.

1088
01:37:12,026 --> 01:37:14,017
Good morning.
Can I help you?

1089
01:37:14,995 --> 01:37:18,761
Well, actually, we wanted
to speak to Mr. Duvernois.

1090
01:37:20,701 --> 01:37:22,566
He's my son.

1091
01:37:24,872 --> 01:37:26,703
He's very shy.

1092
01:37:29,109 --> 01:37:31,339
Mr. Duvernois isn't here
right now.

1093
01:37:31,412 --> 01:37:34,848
But, first of all, do you know
what cryonization is?

1094
01:37:34,949 --> 01:37:36,678
Well, more or less.

1095
01:37:36,750 --> 01:37:40,709
Here are some leaflets.
You can read them while you're waiting.

1096
01:37:40,821 --> 01:37:43,688
One of my colleagues
will be with you soon.

1097
01:37:43,791 --> 01:37:44,849
Thankyou.

1098
01:37:44,925 --> 01:37:48,952
"Live without limits.
Tomorrow is for the foresighted."

1099
01:37:49,063 --> 01:37:50,963
What is this?
Some kind of sect?

1100
01:37:51,098 --> 01:37:55,535
"Cryonization is the biostasis
or preservation of human beings.

1101
01:37:55,603 --> 01:37:59,004
It is the bridge to carry
our patients to a future...

1102
01:37:59,106 --> 01:38:02,075
when technology
will restore them to life."

1103
01:38:05,813 --> 01:38:08,043
You pay to live eternally.

1104
01:38:11,051 --> 01:38:12,814
They laughed at Jules Verne.

1105
01:38:12,887 --> 01:38:16,550
Cesar, all this
is absolutely impossible.

1106
01:38:16,657 --> 01:38:18,625
What do you know
of the future?

1107
01:38:18,759 --> 01:38:22,354
They promise what the Church
has always promised.

1108
01:38:22,463 --> 01:38:24,863
Immortality.
Except they're quacks, not priests.

1109
01:38:24,899 --> 01:38:26,958
How are you involved?

1110
01:38:27,101 --> 01:38:29,535
You're not cryonized.
You're alive.

1111
01:38:29,603 --> 01:38:32,504
This is the contract,
ifyou want to look at it.

1112
01:38:34,041 --> 01:38:36,839
The procedure is very simple.
You could die at any time.

1113
01:38:36,944 --> 01:38:39,777
Today, tomorrow, in 20 years.
It doesn't matter to us.

1114
01:38:39,880 --> 01:38:43,441
At the very moment
you're declared legally dead...

1115
01:38:43,550 --> 01:38:47,452
Life Extension transfers your body
to our store in Arizona.

1116
01:38:47,554 --> 01:38:50,045
There, it's frozen
at minus 78 degrees.

1117
01:38:50,124 --> 01:38:53,958
We call that "total suspension,"
and it costs $240,000.

1118
01:38:54,061 --> 01:38:57,394
30,000 pays for the freezing process,
and the rest...

1119
01:38:57,498 --> 01:38:59,523
goes into
an investment fund...

1120
01:38:59,667 --> 01:39:02,227
the interests from which
pay for maintenance...

1121
01:39:02,369 --> 01:39:05,497
and resurrection costs,
the day that it's possible.

1122
01:39:05,606 --> 01:39:07,403
If it is possible.

1123
01:39:07,474 --> 01:39:11,706
We believe that the reanimation
of the dead will be possible.

1124
01:39:11,779 --> 01:39:13,770
- What's this?
- What?

1125
01:39:13,881 --> 01:39:16,281
Clause 1 4.
Artificial perception.

1126
01:39:16,383 --> 01:39:20,843
It's a concept that we haven't
fully developed yet.

1127
01:39:20,955 --> 01:39:23,617
Look. This is a life.

1128
01:39:23,724 --> 01:39:25,624
Birth and death.

1129
01:39:25,759 --> 01:39:28,751
Let's say you've got
a terminal illness.

1130
01:39:28,896 --> 01:39:32,730
Of course you want to go on living,
but not in the future.

1131
01:39:32,833 --> 01:39:37,133
That doesn't interest you.
You want to live your life now.

1132
01:39:37,204 --> 01:39:40,435
Very well.
You die, we freeze you...

1133
01:39:40,507 --> 01:39:44,967
and when we can resuscitate you,
we'll have you live...

1134
01:39:45,746 --> 01:39:47,008
a dream.

1135
01:39:48,515 --> 01:39:51,177
- A dream?
- It will all look real.

1136
01:39:51,285 --> 01:39:53,480
Your family and friends,
your city...

1137
01:39:53,554 --> 01:39:55,488
the world, even this office.

1138
01:39:55,589 --> 01:39:57,523
But it'll be a virtual reality.

1139
01:39:57,624 --> 01:40:01,321
What's more, we'll make you forget
that you've died...

1140
01:40:01,428 --> 01:40:03,362
and that you signed
this contract.

1141
01:40:03,430 --> 01:40:05,193
- How?
- Very simple.

1142
01:40:05,332 --> 01:40:07,323
Wiping it from your memory.

1143
01:40:07,434 --> 01:40:10,301
You'll live your life linearly,
as if nothing had happened.

1144
01:40:10,404 --> 01:40:14,170
And best of all, you'll live it
as you like, as you wish.

1145
01:40:14,241 --> 01:40:16,709
You'll decide at all times.

1146
01:40:16,777 --> 01:40:20,713
But what ifthere were mistakes?

1147
01:40:20,781 --> 01:40:24,376
What if the dream
was transformed into a nightmare?

1148
01:40:24,485 --> 01:40:27,511
Well, the subconscious
can always play a dirty trick.

1149
01:40:27,588 --> 01:40:31,149
But we're not cowboys.
This is a serious company.

1150
01:40:31,258 --> 01:40:35,592
And virtual reality technology
is constantly making huge advances.

1151
01:40:35,729 --> 01:40:37,720
Look.

1152
01:40:37,865 --> 01:40:39,594
I'll be honest.

1153
01:40:40,734 --> 01:40:43,760
Signing Clause 1 4
is like signing for paradise.

1154
01:40:44,872 --> 01:40:50,469
It's hard to believe.
But they laughed at Jules Verne.

1155
01:40:55,315 --> 01:40:56,373
Excuse me.

1156
01:41:01,321 --> 01:41:04,154
- Where are you going so fast?
- To the bathroom.

1157
01:41:04,258 --> 01:41:06,886
- Well, not so fast.
- I'll go with him.

1158
01:41:06,994 --> 01:41:09,462
He just felt ill, don't worry.

1159
01:41:15,502 --> 01:41:17,470
Cesar, calm down, please.

1160
01:41:17,571 --> 01:41:19,937
This is a dream.
It's the only explanation.

1161
01:41:20,040 --> 01:41:22,008
What he said is impossible.

1162
01:41:22,142 --> 01:41:24,474
In the 20th century,
but maybe not in the 30th.

1163
01:41:24,578 --> 01:41:27,979
- Maybe not, but we're in 1 997.
- That's what it seems.

1164
01:41:28,082 --> 01:41:31,051
- I paid for it to seem like that.
- Listen! If this is a dream--

1165
01:41:31,151 --> 01:41:35,315
Look at me! If this is a dream,
it means that I don't exist!

1166
01:41:35,422 --> 01:41:37,754
- I just imagine you.
- No!

1167
01:41:37,858 --> 01:41:41,294
- Cesar, I'm real.
- How do I know that?

1168
01:41:41,361 --> 01:41:45,320
Can't you tell a dream from reality?
Is this a dream, eh?

1169
01:41:45,466 --> 01:41:47,832
Tell me, is this a dream?

1170
01:41:50,437 --> 01:41:52,962
Cesar, I'm wearing myself out
over this case.

1171
01:41:53,073 --> 01:41:56,668
There is no case. I didn't kill anyone.
It's all a nightmare.

1172
01:41:56,743 --> 01:42:00,270
Fuck it, Cesar, trust me!
This isn't a dream.

1173
01:42:00,380 --> 01:42:02,280
- They got it wrong.
- Who?

1174
01:42:02,382 --> 01:42:07,251
I don't know! But they mixed up Sofia
and Nuria! I see a face that isn't mine.

1175
01:42:07,321 --> 01:42:10,154
I'm sick of hearing that!
Your face is fine.

1176
01:42:10,257 --> 01:42:13,715
You're behaving like a child,
hiding behind that mask.

1177
01:42:13,861 --> 01:42:16,796
- Go on, take it off!
- I don't want to see myself!

1178
01:42:16,864 --> 01:42:19,332
I don't care about that.
I want to see you.

1179
01:42:19,433 --> 01:42:23,631
Don't you realize? All that matters
is what I see! It's my dream!

1180
01:42:23,704 --> 01:42:28,334
Say that once more and
I'll have you locked up in an asylum.

1181
01:42:28,442 --> 01:42:32,344
Show me your face.
Now. You owe it to me.

1182
01:42:52,499 --> 01:42:57,596
Cesar, look in the mirror and tell me
ifyou thinkyou're disfigured.

1183
01:43:02,209 --> 01:43:03,267
God!

1184
01:43:03,377 --> 01:43:05,777
Why do you keep seeing
what isn't there?

1185
01:43:05,879 --> 01:43:08,040
- You look fine.
- I'm a monster!

1186
01:43:08,148 --> 01:43:11,675
What do you mean?
Anybody'd like to have your face.

1187
01:43:11,785 --> 01:43:13,514
You look normal.

1188
01:43:13,587 --> 01:43:16,351
Not just normal.
You're handsome!

1189
01:43:17,558 --> 01:43:21,517
Cesar, listen. Maybe you've got
something like anorexia.

1190
01:43:21,595 --> 01:43:24,996
Some girls insist they're fat
and end up crazy.

1191
01:43:25,098 --> 01:43:26,122
Cesar!

1192
01:43:28,135 --> 01:43:30,194
I want to wake up!

1193
01:43:30,337 --> 01:43:32,999
I want to wake up!

1194
01:43:33,106 --> 01:43:35,973
- Hold it!
- I want to wake up!

1195
01:43:36,109 --> 01:43:37,474
Fuck!

1196
01:43:38,378 --> 01:43:39,572
Shit!

1197
01:43:39,680 --> 01:43:42,308
- Freeze!
- Don't shoot!

1198
01:43:43,483 --> 01:43:46,782
This is a nightmare!
It's a nightmare!

1199
01:43:58,699 --> 01:44:02,692
You! Wait a minute!
You're not to leave!

1200
01:44:02,769 --> 01:44:04,236
Stop!

1201
01:44:13,280 --> 01:44:15,840
Wait a minute!

1202
01:44:31,498 --> 01:44:32,931
It's a dream!

1203
01:44:33,000 --> 01:44:35,298
It's a dream!

1204
01:44:51,952 --> 01:44:56,912
Don't move!
Drop the gun!

1205
01:44:59,293 --> 01:45:02,387
- I want to wake up. I want to wake up.
- Don't move!

1206
01:45:02,496 --> 01:45:05,954
I want to wake up!

1207
01:45:16,710 --> 01:45:18,473
Antonio.

1208
01:45:20,380 --> 01:45:21,813
Antonio!

1209
01:45:23,183 --> 01:45:25,083
What?

1210
01:45:25,185 --> 01:45:27,312
You're crushing me.

1211
01:45:28,588 --> 01:45:32,649
I'd better not move.
I've been shot in the back.

1212
01:45:33,927 --> 01:45:36,020
How do you know?

1213
01:45:37,230 --> 01:45:39,824
Well...

1214
01:45:39,900 --> 01:45:41,299
because--

1215
01:45:55,115 --> 01:45:57,879
What's going on here?

1216
01:45:57,951 --> 01:45:59,976
What the fuck's going on?

1217
01:46:00,087 --> 01:46:01,884
I told you, it's a dream.

1218
01:46:02,022 --> 01:46:04,252
Shut up! Shut up!

1219
01:46:06,259 --> 01:46:10,355
I know what this is.
It's one of those Candid Camera jokes.

1220
01:46:11,264 --> 01:46:14,290
You did a great job, I loved it,
but enough's enough!

1221
01:46:14,401 --> 01:46:16,869
- I see someone.
- Where?

1222
01:46:16,970 --> 01:46:18,995
Up there, on the roof.

1223
01:46:19,139 --> 01:46:21,403
I can't see a thing.

1224
01:46:22,275 --> 01:46:24,539
Where are you going?

1225
01:46:26,847 --> 01:46:31,375
Come on, Antonio. Don't think
about it anymore oryou'll go crazy.

1226
01:46:47,634 --> 01:46:49,226
Hello, Cesar.

1227
01:46:51,138 --> 01:46:53,106
It's time I introduced myself.

1228
01:46:53,240 --> 01:46:56,903
My name is Serge Duvernois.
I represent Life Extension.

1229
01:46:56,977 --> 01:46:58,376
We met...

1230
01:46:59,579 --> 01:47:00,910
1 50 years ago.

1231
01:47:01,014 --> 01:47:03,710
What? Has the world gone mad?

1232
01:47:03,817 --> 01:47:07,514
There's no world.
It's all in that gentleman's mind.

1233
01:47:07,587 --> 01:47:09,521
Including you and me.

1234
01:47:09,589 --> 01:47:12,387
Sure! Shall I thump you
to see if it hurts?

1235
01:47:12,492 --> 01:47:17,589
Try it. They can make you disappear
right now, like everyone else.

1236
01:47:17,731 --> 01:47:20,598
- And who are "they," may I ask?
- The company.

1237
01:47:20,700 --> 01:47:23,032
Life Extension.

1238
01:47:23,136 --> 01:47:25,536
They know everything
we're saying.

1239
01:47:25,639 --> 01:47:31,305
They know what is going through Cesar's
mind an instant after he thinks it.

1240
01:47:31,411 --> 01:47:34,938
If they can make me disappear,
why haven't they done it?

1241
01:47:35,048 --> 01:47:37,039
It would be virtually incorrect.

1242
01:47:37,150 --> 01:47:39,277
You've just saved his life.

1243
01:47:39,386 --> 01:47:42,947
Virtually incorrect?
Do you think I'm an idiot or what?

1244
01:47:43,056 --> 01:47:46,583
No, quite the opposite.
You're a great guy.

1245
01:47:46,693 --> 01:47:49,491
A character who is
very necessary for Cesar.

1246
01:47:50,564 --> 01:47:52,293
A character?

1247
01:47:53,533 --> 01:47:55,433
- Where are you going?
- To look for someone.

1248
01:47:55,535 --> 01:47:59,027
There is no one.
People aren't necessary now.

1249
01:48:06,813 --> 01:48:08,838
Why didn't you wake me before?

1250
01:48:09,983 --> 01:48:13,544
You only had to ask.
But that was difficult.

1251
01:48:13,653 --> 01:48:17,612
Because, in theory,
you wouldn't know you were dreaming.

1252
01:48:17,757 --> 01:48:19,452
Since when?

1253
01:48:19,593 --> 01:48:21,618
Remember the day
of the discotheque?

1254
01:48:21,761 --> 01:48:25,595
That night, when you fell asleep
on the sidewalk...

1255
01:48:25,699 --> 01:48:28,167
was the one chosen
for the splice.

1256
01:48:28,268 --> 01:48:29,860
What splice?

1257
01:48:29,970 --> 01:48:33,462
The splice between your real life
andyour virtual life.

1258
01:48:33,540 --> 01:48:37,135
A splice of 1 50 years
which you didn 't notice...

1259
01:48:37,210 --> 01:48:40,611
because you were dead
and frozen.

1260
01:48:40,714 --> 01:48:42,705
From when you woke up...

1261
01:48:42,816 --> 01:48:45,011
nothing was real.

1262
01:48:45,118 --> 01:48:48,246
We wiped what really happened
from your memory.

1263
01:48:49,556 --> 01:48:52,150
What was it?

1264
01:48:52,225 --> 01:48:54,716
You never saw Sofia again.

1265
01:48:54,828 --> 01:48:58,093
And the doctors were never able
to rebuild your face.

1266
01:48:59,299 --> 01:49:03,497
You woke up on that street
with an awful hangover.

1267
01:49:03,603 --> 01:49:05,935
You shutyourselfaway
for months.

1268
01:49:06,039 --> 01:49:08,007
One dayyou learned
that we existed.

1269
01:49:09,075 --> 01:49:12,533
You came to the office,
you signed the contract...

1270
01:49:12,646 --> 01:49:14,876
and then...

1271
01:49:14,981 --> 01:49:16,949
you killedyourself.

1272
01:49:18,418 --> 01:49:20,249
I paid for this?

1273
01:49:21,288 --> 01:49:24,815
I paid for Nuria
to come back as Sofia?

1274
01:49:24,891 --> 01:49:27,155
I paid to look like
a monster again?

1275
01:49:27,227 --> 01:49:29,195
I paid to live this nightmare?

1276
01:49:29,329 --> 01:49:32,025
You paid to live
whatever you wanted.

1277
01:49:32,132 --> 01:49:34,396
We just provided the setting
and the characters.

1278
01:49:34,501 --> 01:49:36,901
You invented your hell.

1279
01:49:37,003 --> 01:49:39,699
I tried to warn you
in that bar.

1280
01:49:39,773 --> 01:49:41,900
I said it all depended
on your mind.

1281
01:49:42,809 --> 01:49:45,744
Do I just have to want it?

1282
01:49:45,845 --> 01:49:48,473
- Can Antonio come--
- There's no one here.

1283
01:49:49,382 --> 01:49:52,579
They can't have made
4 million people disappear!

1284
01:49:53,853 --> 01:49:55,912
You've overcome your fears.

1285
01:49:56,022 --> 01:49:58,081
Ifyou want,
we can try again...

1286
01:49:58,191 --> 01:50:00,352
have you live
a wonderful dream...

1287
01:50:00,460 --> 01:50:04,191
with money, friends, Sofia,
or whatever girl you want.

1288
01:50:04,331 --> 01:50:06,799
You just have to ask.

1289
01:50:08,668 --> 01:50:10,602
I don't want more dreams.

1290
01:50:10,670 --> 01:50:12,729
It isn't a dream!

1291
01:50:12,839 --> 01:50:14,739
Cesar, listen to me.

1292
01:50:14,841 --> 01:50:17,332
This is real.
This man is a sham.

1293
01:50:17,444 --> 01:50:19,969
Let's go down
and look for people.

1294
01:50:20,046 --> 01:50:22,776
Ignore him. It's logical
for him to behave like this...

1295
01:50:22,849 --> 01:50:25,340
but he doesn't
feel anything.

1296
01:50:25,452 --> 01:50:27,682
I don't feel anything?

1297
01:50:27,787 --> 01:50:31,314
I don't feel anything?
What do you know about what I feel?

1298
01:50:31,424 --> 01:50:33,119
Ignore him, he isn't real.

1299
01:50:33,193 --> 01:50:35,855
Yes, I am real!

1300
01:50:35,962 --> 01:50:38,192
I've got a wife
and two daughters.

1301
01:50:38,331 --> 01:50:42,267
His personality is designed
so that he'll say all this now.

1302
01:50:42,402 --> 01:50:45,371
Where are my daughters?
God!

1303
01:50:45,438 --> 01:50:48,498
Cesar, we can offeryou
another possibility.

1304
01:50:48,575 --> 01:50:51,806
In 1 997, it was impossible
to rebuild your face.

1305
01:50:51,911 --> 01:50:55,540
But out there,
it's the year 2 1 45.

1306
01:50:55,649 --> 01:50:58,982
You wouldn't believe
the things surgery can do.

1307
01:50:59,085 --> 01:51:01,349
You could wake up...

1308
01:51:01,454 --> 01:51:04,287
and live in the future
like a normal person.

1309
01:51:04,357 --> 01:51:07,520
- In the future?
- You have to choose.

1310
01:51:10,563 --> 01:51:12,497
How could I wake up?

1311
01:51:12,565 --> 01:51:16,763
How would you wake
from your worst nightmare?

1312
01:51:22,909 --> 01:51:24,843
No, Cesar, don't listen to him!

1313
01:51:24,911 --> 01:51:28,210
Your partners set this up!
They want you to kill yourself!

1314
01:51:28,281 --> 01:51:31,773
He's done that.
Now it'll just be a formality.

1315
01:51:33,153 --> 01:51:35,644
- I'm going to do it.
- Very well.

1316
01:51:36,990 --> 01:51:41,154
Do you have any wish
before you die?

1317
01:51:55,475 --> 01:51:58,137
Let them out there read my mind.

1318
01:53:02,142 --> 01:53:03,541
Who are you?

1319
01:53:04,844 --> 01:53:06,436
I don't know.

1320
01:53:06,546 --> 01:53:10,038
Don't keep suffering.
It's all in your head.

1321
01:53:10,150 --> 01:53:12,618
It's all psychological.

1322
01:53:38,812 --> 01:53:40,712
Come on, Cesar.

1323
01:53:54,527 --> 01:53:57,826
- What will happen to them?
- Don't prolong this farewell.

1324
01:53:57,931 --> 01:54:01,332
You think they're your friends,
but they're just images.

1325
01:54:01,467 --> 01:54:03,458
That man isn't really crying.

1326
01:54:26,993 --> 01:54:31,020
- I forgot, I get vertigo.
- Then don't look.

1327
01:54:33,266 --> 01:54:34,756
Good-bye, Cesar.

1328
01:55:18,378 --> 01:55:19,777
Relax.

1329
01:55:22,048 --> 01:55:23,447
Relax.

1330
01:55:26,019 --> 01:55:27,987
Open your eyes.

